{
  "texts": [
    "According to Boyd et al. (1982), in developed countries, around 75% of all psychiatric admissions are young adults with depression.",
    "The fourth leading cause of death in young adults is suicide, which is closely related to untreated depression (World Health Organization, 2023).",
    "Moreover, traditional survey-based depression screening may be in-effective due to the cognitive bias of the patients who may not be truthful in revealing their depression condition.",
    "So there is a huge need for an effective, inexpensive and almost real time intervention for depression in this high risk population.",
    "Interestingly, among young adults, social media is very popular where they share their day to day activities and the availability of social media services is growing exponentially year by year (O' Keeffe & Clarke-Pearson, 2011)."
  ]
}